                <div class="faq-a">ETFs (like VOO or SPLG) are generally more tax-efficient in taxable accounts. Mutual funds (like FXAIX or SWPPX) allow for exact dollar-amount investing and automatic investments, making them ideal for tax-advantaged retirement accounts like a 401(k) or IRA.</div>
            </div>

